trans-unit.source: Represents the result of mapping a string to its sort key.
trans-unit.target: Representerer resultatet av å tilordne en streng til sorteringsnøkkelen.

trans-unit.source: A culture-sensitive comparison of two strings depends on each character in the strings having several categories of sort weights, including script, alphabetic, case, and diacritic weights.
trans-unit.target: Kulturen sikkerhetsfølsom sammenligning av to strenger avhenger av hvert tegn i strenger har flere kategorier av sortering vekt og inkludert skript, bokstaver, små og diakritisk vekten.

trans-unit.source: A sort key serves as the repository of these weights for a particular string.
trans-unit.target: En sorteringsnøkkel fungerer som lager for disse vekten for en bestemt streng.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method returns an instance of the SortKey class that reflects the culture-sensitive mapping of characters in a specified string.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metoden returnerer en forekomst av klassen SortKey som gjenspeiler kultur sikkerhetsfølsom tilordning av tegn i en angitt streng.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: The value of a SortKey object is its key data, which is returned by the <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.KeyData%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Verdien for et objekt for SortKey er de viktige dataene, som er returnert av den <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.KeyData%2A>egenskapen.</xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.KeyData%2A>

trans-unit.source: This key data consists of a series of bytes that encode the string, culture-specific sorting rules, and user-specified comparison options.
trans-unit.target: Denne nøkkelen data består av en rekke byte som kode streng, kultur sortering regler og brukerangitte sammenligningen alternativer.

trans-unit.source: A comparison using sort keys consists of a bitwise comparison of the corresponding key data in each sort key.
trans-unit.target: En sammenligning med sorteringsnøkler består av en bitvis sammenligning av de tilsvarende nøkkel dataene i hver enkelt sorteringsnøkkel.

trans-unit.source: For example, if you create a sort key by calling the <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29> method with a value of <xref:System.Globalization.CompareOptions?displayProperty=fullName>, a string comparison operation that uses the sort key is case-insensitive.
trans-unit.target: Hvis for eksempel, du opprette en sorteringsnøkkel ved å kalle den <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29>metoden med verdien <xref:System.Globalization.CompareOptions?displayProperty=fullName>, operasjonen for sammenligning en streng som bruker sorteringsnøkkelen skiller ikke mellom.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareOptions?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29>

trans-unit.source: After you create a sort key for a string, you compare sort keys by calling the static <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method.
trans-unit.target: Når du oppretter en sorteringsnøkkel for en streng, du sammenligne sorteringsnøkler ved å kalle statiske <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metode.</xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: This method performs a simple byte-by-byte comparison, so it is much faster than the <xref:System.String.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> or <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden utfører en enkel byte for byte sammenligning, slik det er mye raskere enn den <xref:System.String.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>eller <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metode.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.String.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Performance considerations When performing a string comparison, the <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A> and <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> methods yield the same results, but they target different scenarios.
trans-unit.target: Av sikkerhetshensyn ved utføring av en strengsammenligning den <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A>og <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metoder gi samme resultat, men de target forskjellige scenarier.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A>

trans-unit.source: At a high level, the <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method generates the sort key for each string, performs the comparison, and then discards the sort key and returns the result of the comparison.
trans-unit.target: Fra et høyere nivå av <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metoden genererer sorteringsnøkkel for hver streng, utfører sammenligning av sorteringsnøkkel, forkastes, og returnerer resultatet av sammenligningen.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: However, the <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method actually doesn't generate an entire sort key to perform the comparison.
trans-unit.target: Imidlertid den <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metoden faktisk ikke generere en hele sorteringsnøkkel for å utføre sammenligningen.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Instead, the method generates the key data for each text element (that is, base character, surrogate pair, or combining character sequence) in each string.
trans-unit.target: Metoden genererer i stedet viktige dataene for hvert element i teksten (det vil si base tegn, erstatningspar eller å kombinere tegnsekvensen) i hver streng.

trans-unit.source: The method then compares the key data for the corresponding text elements.
trans-unit.target: Metoden sammenligner viktige dataene for de tilhørende teksten-elementene.

trans-unit.source: The operation terminates as soon as the ultimate result of the comparison is determined.
trans-unit.target: Operasjonen avslutter som ultimate resultatet av sammenligningen, bestemmes.

trans-unit.source: Sort key information is computed, but no SortKey object is created.
trans-unit.target: Sorter nøkkelinformasjon er beregnet, men ingen SortKey-objektet er opprettet.

trans-unit.source: This strategy is economical in terms of performance if both strings are compared once, but becomes expensive if the same strings are compared many times.
trans-unit.target: Denne fremgangsmåten er økonomisk når det gjelder hvis begge strenger sammenlignes én gang, men blir kostbar hvis de samme strengene sammenlignes mange ganger.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A> method requires generation of a SortKey object for each string before performing the comparison.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A>metoden krever generering av et SortKey-objekt for hver streng før du utfører sammenligningen.</xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.Compare%2A>

trans-unit.source: This strategy is expensive in terms of performance for the first comparison because of the time and memory invested to generate the SortKey objects.
trans-unit.target: Denne fremgangsmåten er kostbar når det gjelder for den første sammenligningen på grunn av tid og minne brukt for å generere SortKey-objekter.

trans-unit.source: However, it becomes economical if the same sort keys are compared many times.
trans-unit.target: Det blir imidlertid økonomisk Hvis samme sorteringsnøkler sammenlignes mange ganger.

trans-unit.source: For example, suppose you write an application that searches a database table for the row in which the string-based index column matches a specified search string.
trans-unit.target: Anta at du skriver et program som søker i en tabell for rad der strengen-basert indekskolonne samsvarer med en angitte søkestrengen.

trans-unit.source: The table contains thousands of rows, and comparing the search string to the index in each row will take a long time.
trans-unit.target: Tabellen inneholder tusenvis av rader, og sammenligne søkestrengen i indeksen i hver rad tar lang tid.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, when the application stores a row and its index column, it also generates and stores the sort key for the index in a column dedicated to improving search performance.
trans-unit.target: Derfor når programmet inneholder en rad- og tilhørende indeksen, i tillegg genererer og lagrer sorteringsnøkkel for indeksen i en kolonne som er reservert for å forbedre ytelsen på søket.

trans-unit.source: When the application searches for a target row, it compares the sort key for the search string to the sort key for the index string, instead of comparing the search string to the index string.
trans-unit.target: Når programmet søker etter en målrad, sammenlignes sorteringsnøkkel for søkestrengen til sorteringsnøkkel for strengen indeks i stedet for sammenligning av søkestrengen til indeksen-streng.

trans-unit.source: Security considerations The <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName> method returns a SortKey object with the value based on a specified string and <xref:System.Globalization.CompareOptions> value, and the culture associated with the underlying <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo> object.
trans-unit.target: Sikkerhetshensyn den <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName>metoden returnerer et SortKey-objekt med verdien som er basert på en angitt streng og <xref:System.Globalization.CompareOptions>verdien og kulturen som er knyttet til den underliggende <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo>objektet.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo> </xref:System.Globalization.CompareOptions> </xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If a security decision depends on a string comparison or case change, you should use the <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName> method of the invariant culture to ensure that the behavior of the operation is consistent, regardless of the culture settings of the operating system.
trans-unit.target: Hvis en beslutningen sikkerhet, avhengig av en strengsammenligning eller små endring, bør du bruke den <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName>metoden for den konstante kulturen å sikre at virkemåten til operasjonen er konsekvent, uavhengig av kulturen innstillingene for operativsystemet.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Use the following steps to obtain a sort key: 1.
trans-unit.target: Bruk følgende til å hente en sorteringsnøkkel: 1.

trans-unit.source: Retrieve the invariant culture from the <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture?displayProperty=fullName> property.
trans-unit.target: Henter den konstante kulturen fra den <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen.</xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Retrieve a <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo> object for the invariant culture from the <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CompareInfo%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property.
trans-unit.target: Hente en <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo>objekt for den konstante kulturen fra den <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CompareInfo%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen.</xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CompareInfo%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo>

trans-unit.source: Call the <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName> method.
trans-unit.target: Kall den <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName>metoden.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.GetSortKey%28System.String%2CSystem.Globalization.CompareOptions%29?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Working with the value of a SortKey object is equivalent to calling the Windows `LCMapString` method with the LCMAP_SORTKEY value specified.
trans-unit.target: Arbeide med verdien for en SortKey objektet tilsvarer kaller Windows `LCMapString` metode med LCMAP_SORTKEY-verdien som er angitt.

trans-unit.source: However, for the SortKey object, the sort keys for English characters precede the sort keys for Korean characters.
trans-unit.target: For SortKey-objektet foran sorteringsnøkler for engelske tegn sorteringsnøkler for koreansk tegn.

trans-unit.source: SortKey objects can be serialized, but only so that they can cross <xref:System.AppDomain> objects.
trans-unit.target: SortKey objekter kan være serialiserte, men bare slik at de kan cross <xref:System.AppDomain>objekter.</xref:System.AppDomain>

trans-unit.source: If an application serializes a SortKey object, the application must regenerate all the sort keys when there is a new version of the .NET Framework.
trans-unit.target: Hvis et program serializes et SortKey-objekt, må programmet generere alle sorteringsnøkler når det er en ny versjon av .NET Framework.

trans-unit.source: For more information about sort keys, see Unicode Technical Standard #10, "Unicode Collation Algorithm" on the [Unicode Consortium website](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=37123).
trans-unit.target: Du finner mer informasjon om sorteringsnøkler se Unicode teknisk Standard 10, "Unicode sortering algoritmen" på den [Unicode Consortium webområdet](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=37123).

trans-unit.source: Compares two sort keys.
trans-unit.target: Sammenligner to sorteringsnøkler.

trans-unit.source: The Compare method compares the <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.KeyData%2A> properties of the `sortkey1` and `sortkey2` parameters.
trans-unit.target: Metoden sammenligne sammenligner den <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.KeyData%2A>egenskapene for den `sortkey1` og `sortkey2` parametere.</xref:System.Globalization.SortKey.KeyData%2A>

trans-unit.source: The method yields the same results as the <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method.
trans-unit.target: Metoden gir samme resultat som den <xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>metoden.</xref:System.Globalization.CompareInfo.Compare%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: For more information about the Compare method and the comparison of sort keys, see the <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey> class topic.
trans-unit.target: Du finner mer informasjon om metoden sammenligne og sammenligning av sorteringsnøkler av <xref:System.Globalization.SortKey>klassen emnet.</xref:System.Globalization.SortKey>
